The Third Force Mega Movement under the auspices of the National Consultative Front (NCFront) has vowed to sponsor credible candidates for the 2023 elections in its effort to actualise its “rescue Nigeria” mission. To this end, the movement has called on interested credible Nigerians, members, supporters, allies and friends, who may wish to vie for any of the elective offices in the 2023 general elections (as listed by INEC) on the platform of the Third Force Mega Party to apply. COVID 19: FG lifts curfew, crowd restrictions SDP governorship candidate, Oni, escapes attack in Ekiti Daily Trust reports that there is anxiety in the polity ahead of the floating of the mega platform. Already, a key member of the Third Force Movement and former governor, Sen. Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso, has quit and joined the New Nigeria People’s Party (NNPP). It was however learnt that the Movement, which has Prof. Pat Utomi, Prof. Attahiru Jega, among others as leaders, would unveil the Mega Party by the middle of April. In a notice yesterday, the movement said in accordance with its founding political testament and mandate, it “is now set to sponsor credible candidates for the 2023 elections towards the realization of its rescue mission for Nigeria and therefore is commencing a serious search and recruitment in that regard.”